
[1]depuration

   DEPURATION, n.

   1. The act of purifying or freeing fluids from heterogeneous matter.
   This is done by decantation, when the feculent matter is deposited on
   the bottom of the vessel; or by despumation, effected by boiling or
   fermentation, and skimming; or by filtration; or by fining or
   clarification.

   2. The cleansing of a wound from impure matter.
